reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Grandkids Loved Them, All 18 Cars Worked, Smashing Success At Party
reviews.reviewText: When I learned that 8 of my grandkids would be at a family party all at the same time, I started filling goodie-bags with toys & treats, as Grandmas do. Luckily I had plenty of time to order these cars before the party.I honestly didn't expect much from them. Most of the time, party favors are cheap little disposable light plastic things. But the quality of these cars really exceeded my expectations, and when I tested each car when I received the box, every single one of them worked great. I'll admit I spent a little more time "test playing" with them than I probably should have! (wink)Anyway, since the goodie-bags were already overflowing, I figured I'd put all 18 cars in the included cloth bag, and let each child pick 2 cars out of the bag. This was a big hit, and they all loved getting the cars this way.All the cars survived several hours of play at the party, so to me that's a big win, especially since they're not as high quality as something like matchbox cars. I don't expect party favors to last long, but I think these will be kept a lot longer than usual. At about $15 for the whole batch when I ordered, I thought it was more than I normally would spend, but it turned out to be a much better value than I anticipated. Plus, there were 2 left over for Grandma & Grandpa to play with after all 8 grandkids had 2 cars apiece. Perfect!Value, decent quality, function, happy grandkids, great big success....This earns 5 vrooming stars from me!

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A lot of fun with the toy cars
reviews.reviewText: I purchased these toy cars for my toddler boy, which bring him plenty of fun and imaginative adventures.Once I opened the box of these toy cars, it includes 9 vivid pull back cars and a storage bag. These cars are in a variety of bright colors, which attracts my boy’s attention and excite him a lot. I also appreciate the bag it provided, which solve the problem to restore these cars. By the way, this bag could restore some more extra model cars, it is a thoughtful consideration.These pull back cars are powered without batteries, which just need simple pull backs. I showed my boy how to pull cars back and release, he will manage it for several times, and then he could make these cars moved smoothly by himself. In addition, the size of these cars are quite convenient and safe to my kid, he could hold these cars tightly with his small hands, and it is too big to fit into his mouth. My boy loves playing with these toy cars and gets a lot of fun with them.
